column6: Description

The layer consists of points that represent wind turbines in different stages of design and construction. The status levels are: Built (Uppförda): Wind turbines are physically present on site; Dealt with (Handläggs): The Authority is dealing with the matter, but has not yet made its decision. Granted (Beviljade): The Authority has said yes to wind power establishment, but no wind turbines have yet been built. Rejected/Denied (Avslagna/Nekade): The Authority has rejected the proposed wind farm establishment. Appeal  (överklagade): An appeal has been lodged and a final decision has not been registered for the type of action. No longer up-to-date/withdrawn (Inte längre aktuella/återkallade): Wind turbines are no longer pending. Data is missing (Uppgift saknas): Data to assess status are not filled in in Vindbrukskollen. Dismantled (Nedmonterade): Wind turbines have been present on site, but have been assembled down.
Subset of wind_turbines_Vindbrukskollen_2020, considering only turbines in operation

column4: Distance from wind turbines in operation
column6: Distance from the nearest wind turbine in operation, in meters.

The layer consists of polygons for areas that are designated as national interests for wind farm (electricity production from wind power). The theme has been obtained from The Swedish Energy Agency. The first areas of national interest were established in 2004, but have then revised in installments. The latest update was made in 2013 and one additional decisions were made in 2015 for a small number of areas.
The layer consists of lines representing local (“stam”) and regional power lines.
Distance from the nearest power line, in meters.
The layer consists of polygons representing areas with mining consession in operation.
The layer consists of polygons approved for mining, or where there was mining in the past, where the vegetation was suppressed. They may represent areas where there were disturbances.

The product GSD-Elevation data, grid 50+ nh from the national elevation model (nh) consist of a terrain model, height values with two decimals, in grid form with a resolution of 50 metres.
Slope based on the digital elevation model 50m from Lantmäteriet. Calculated in GRASS GIS using the r.slope.aspect module.
Aspect based on the digital elevation model 50m from Lantmäteriet. Calculated in GRASS GIS using the r.slope.aspect module.
Aspect based on the digital elevation model 50m from Lantmäteriet, classified in 4 directions: 1 = N, 2 = E, 3 = S, 4 = W. Calculated in GRASS GIS using the r.slope.aspect module.

Topografic position index (TPI) based on the digital elevation model 50m from Lantmäteriet. Calculated in GRASS GIS using a function I wrote, based on advice from Stefan Blumentrath (NINA). Multiple sizes for the neighborhood used, defined in the name.
This is a layer corresponding to land cover. It was based on Sentinel-2 sattelite images from 2015-2018, with support for laser/LiDAR data and several other datasets.
This is a layer corresponding to land cover. It was based on Sentinel-2 sattelite images from 2015-2018, with support for laser/LiDAR data and several other datasets.

The theme consists of polygons from the Swedish Board of Agriculture. The theme only shows agricultural land (arable land, pasture) that is eligible under the EU definitions. However, the theme does not show all such agricultural land but only those parts as a farmer sought support at some point.

The theme consists of polygons from Svensk MarktäckeData (SMD) which describe arable land that includes arable land, pastures and fruit and berry cultivation. The theme can be considered to show open agricultural land but regardless of whether this is cultivated or not.

Density of wolverines for each year, calculated based on data from RovBase (rovbase.se) using spatial capture-recapture models.
